@node BRASS "Brassclaw Orcs"

@{b}Brassclaw Orcs@{ub}

Color   = Red
Rarity  = FE(C1/C1/C1/C1)
Type    = Summon Orcs (3/2)
Cost    = 2R
Artist  = Dan Frazier / Heather Hudson / Rob Alexander / Rob Alexander

@{b}NOTE@{ub}: There are FOUR different artworks for this card.

Text(FE): Cannot be assigned to block any creature of power greater than 1.

Flavor Text: @{i}"Brassclaws were typical Orcs - quick to laud their own
              prowess in battle, quick to jeer at their opponents,
              and quicker still to run away when things started to
              look slightly dangerous."
              @{ui}---Sarpadian Empires, vol. IV

Flavor Text: @{i}"The large brass claws worn by some Sarpadian Orc tribes
              were among the least feared weapons ever known."
              @{ui}---Sarpadian Empires, vol. IV

Flavor Text: @{i}"A whole skin is worth a thousand victories."
              ---Orcish Veteran of the Battle of Montford@{ui}

Flavor Text: @{i}"The Brassclaws delighted in lightning raids on Icatian
              and Dwarven towns; an unprepared enemy is easier to defeat."
              @{ui}---Sarpadian Empires, vol. IV

 @{b}NO RULINGS@{ub}

@endnode
@node DWAAR "Dwarven Armorer"

@{b}Dwarven Armorer@{ub}

Color   = Red
Rarity  = FE(U1)
Type    = Summon Dwarf (0/2)
Cost    = R
Artist  = Bryon Wackwitz

Text(FE): <RT>: Discard a card from your hand to put either a +0/+1 or a
          +1/+0 counter on a target creature.

Flavor Text: @{i}"The few remaining pieces from this period suggest the
              Dwarves eventually made weapons and armor out of
              everything, even children's toys."
              @{ui}---Sarpadian Empires, vol. IV

 @{" Rulings " link MTG_CARD_D.guide/DWMOR}

@endnode
