@node GOBGR "Goblin Grenade"

@{b}Goblin Grenade@{ub}

Color   = Red
Rarity  = FE(C1/C1/C1)
Type    = Sorcery
Cost    = R
Artist  = Christopher Rush / Dan Frazier / Ron Spencer

@{b}NOTE@{ub}: There are THREE different artworks for this card.

Text(FE): Sacrifice a Goblin to have Goblin Grenade deal 5 damage to one
          target.

Flavor Text: @{i}"Without their massive numbers, the Goblins could never
              have launched such a successful offensive."
              @{ui}---Sarpadian Empires, vol. VI

Flavor Text: @{i}"I don't suppose we could teach them to
              throw the cursed things?"
              ---Ivra Jursdotter@{ui}

Flavor Text: @{i}"According to accepted theory, the Grenade held some
              kind of flammable mixture and was carried to its
              target by a hapless Goblin."
              @{ui}---Sarpadian Empires, vol. IV

 @{" Rulings " link MTG_CARD_G.guide/GOGRE}

@endnode
@node GOBKI "Goblin Kites"

@{b}Goblin Kites@{ub}

Color   = Red
Rarity  = FE(U3)
Type    = Enchantment
Cost    = 1R
Artist  = Anson Maddocks

Text(FE): <R>: A target creature you control, which cannot have a
          toughness greater than 2, gains flying until end of turn. Other
          effects may later be used to increase the creature's toughness.
          At end of turn, flip a coin; opponent calls heads or tails while
          coin is in the air. If the flip ends up in opponent's favor,
          bury that creature.

 @{" Rulings " link MTG_CARD_G.guide/GOKIT}

@endnode
@node GOBWD "Goblin War Drums"

@{b}Goblin War Drums@{ub}

Color   = Red
Rarity  = FE(C1/C1/C1/C1)
Type    = Enchantment
Cost    = 2R
Artist  = Dan Frazier / Heather Hudson / Jeff A. Menges / Richard Kane Ferguson

@{b}NOTE@{ub}: There are FOUR different artworks for this card.

Text(FE): Each attacking creature you control that opponent chooses to
          block may not be blocked with fewer than two creatures.

Flavor Text: @{i}"The Goblins' dreaded War Drums struck terror into
              the hearts of even their bravest foes."
              @{ui}---Sarpadian Empires, vol. IV

Flavor Text: @{i}The War Drums enabled Goblin and Orcish armies to
             crush the sparsely defended Dwarven cities.@{ui}

Flavor Text: @{i}When creating a new War Drum, Goblin designers sought
             out the highest quality skulls. Serra Angel skulls were
             most highly prized, although most acknowledged that the
             skull of the exotic Sea Serpent made for a richer tone.@{ui}

Flavor Text: @{i}"Defending the outer trenches, we strained our eyes in
              the darkness. All we could hear was the Drums' terrible
              pounding. Dobbs, on my right, broke first. Soon we were
              all heading for the walls."
              ---Corporal Peter Douglas, courtmartial testimony@{ui}

 @{" Rulings " link MTG_CARD_G.guide/GOWDR}

@endnode
