              @{ui}---Sarpadian Empires, vol. IV

 @{" Rulings " link MTG_CARD_G.guide/GOWAR}

@endnode
@node ORCCA "Orcish Captain"

@{b}Orcish Captain@{ub}

Color   = Red
Rarity  = FE(U3)
Type    = Summon Orc (1/1)
Cost    = R
Artist  = Mark Tedin

Text(FE): <1>: Choose a target Orc. Flip a coin; opponent calls heads or
          tails while coin is in the air. If the flip ends up in your
          favor, that Orc gets +2/+0 until end of turn. Otherwise, that
          Orc gets -0/-2 until end of turn.

Flavor Text: @{i}There's a chance to win every battle.@{ui}

 @{" Rulings " link MTG_CARD_O.guide/ORCCA}

@endnode
@node ORCSP "Orcish Spy"

@{b}Orcish Spy@{ub}

Color   = Red
Rarity  = FE(C1/C1/C1)
Type    = Summon Orc (1/1)
Cost    = R
Artist  = Daniel Gelon / Pete Venters / Susan van Camp

@{b}NOTE@{ub}: There are THREE different artworks for this card.

Text(FE): <T>: Look at the top three cards of target player's library and
          return them in the same order.

Flavor Text: @{i}"Orcish armies often employed the smaller, swifter,
              and less intelligent Goblins as spies."
              @{ui}---Sarpadian Empires, vol. I

Flavor Text: @{i}"You idiot! Never let the spies mingle with the Orcish
              regulars after completing a mission. Now we'll never
              get them to fight!"
              ---General Khurzog@{ui}

Flavor Text: @{i}"Yeah, they're ugly, they desert in droves, and their
              personal habits are enough to make you sick. But I'll
              say this for Orcs: they make great spies."
              ---Ivra Jursdotter@{ui}

 @{b}NO RULINGS@{ub}

@endnode
